Aristotle's Ichthyological Contributions
Taxonomic Classification: Aristotle created the first known scientific classification for fish, organizing 117 Mediterranean species based on their characteristics. 
Anatomical and Behavioral Observations: He meticulously documented the anatomical and behavioral differences between various fish and marine mammals, offering a detailed account of the Mediterranean fauna. 
Biological Processes: Aristotle's studies included observations on fish reproduction, feeding habits, migrations, and even diseases. 
Early Marine Biology: He is considered the first ichthyologist, with his work forming the basis for future studies in marine biology and zoology. 
